Oracle AI Database 26ai
True Cache — DBA Setup Guide
Step-by-step configuration for on-premises Linux x86-64 (Release 23.26.1+)

Overview
True Cache is a diskless, read-only Oracle instance that maintains a transactionally consistent replica of the primary database in memory using Redo Apply. Unlike Redis or Memcached, True Cache is fully ACID-compliant — applications see a consistent snapshot without any manual cache invalidation.

Key benefit: The JDBC driver automatically routes read-only transactions to True Cache with zero application code changes. True Cache serves queries from its in-memory buffer cache; blocks not yet cached are fetched on demand from the primary.

How True Cache differs from Active Data Guard
Feature	True Cache	Active Data Guard
Primary purpose	Read offload / low latency	HA failover + read offload
Storage on standby	None (diskless)	Full ASM disk copy
Failover capable	No	Yes
ACID consistent	Yes	Yes
License	Active Data Guard option	Active Data Guard option
Auto JDBC routing	Yes	Yes (read-only service)

